---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import NavRight from '../../components/NavRight.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="auth.md Demo · agents.txt"
  description="Live demonstration of agentic registration over RFC 9728 metadata plus a /auth.md walkthrough: PRM discovery, AS metadata with agent_auth block, register, optional OTP claim ceremony, credential use, revocation."
  canonicalUrl="https://agents-txt.com/demo/authmd"
>
  <!-- Nav -->
  <header class="sticky top-0 z-50 bg-white border-b border-[#e5e5e5]">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 h-14 flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 min-w-0">
        <a href="/" class="flex items-center no-underline shrink-0" aria-label="agents.txt"><img src="/assets/mark-2.svg" alt="agents.txt" width="26" height="26" class="h-[26px] w-[26px]" /></a>
        <span class="text-[#ccc] select-none">/</span>
        <a href="/demo" class="text-sm text-[#555] hover:text-[#111] transition-colors no-underline whitespace-nowrap">Demos</a>
        <span class="text-[#ccc] select-none">/</span>
        <span class="text-sm text-[#111] whitespace-nowrap">auth.md</span>
      </div>
      <NavRight current="demo" />
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Page body -->
  <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 pt-12 pb-24">
    <div class="max-w-[72ch]">

      <!-- Cover -->
      <div class="mb-10 pb-8 border-b border-[#e5e5e5]">
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-[#111] mb-1">
          auth.md: Agentic Registration Walkthrough
        </h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#777] font-mono mb-6">auth-md · RFC 9728 PRM · agent_auth AS metadata block</p>
        <dl class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-x-6 gap-y-2 text-sm">
          <dt class="text-[#999] font-medium">Protocol</dt>
          <dd class="text-[#111]">
            <a href="https://github.com/workos/auth.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="font-mono underline underline-offset-2 decoration-[#bbb] hover:decoration-[#111] transition-all">
              github.com/workos/auth.md
            </a>
          </dd>
          <dt class="text-[#999] font-medium">Discovery</dt>
          <dd class="font-mono text-[#111]">/auth.md · /.well-known/oauth-protected-resource · /agents.json authorization</dd>
          <dt class="text-[#999] font-medium">Underlying standards</dt>
          <dd class="font-mono text-[#111]">RFC 9728 (PRM) · RFC 8414 (AS metadata) · IETF ID-JAG draft</dd>
          <dt class="text-[#999] font-medium">Transport</dt>
          <dd class="text-[#111]">HTTPS · Bearer credential (access_token or api_key)</dd>
          <dt class="text-[#999] font-medium">Status</dt>
          <dd class="text-[#111]">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center border border-[#111] text-[10px] font-semibold tracking-[0.08em] uppercase px-1.5 py-0.5 leading-none mr-2">Discovery</span>
            Walks the discovery surfaces on this server. Registration and claim flows are described, not wired.
          </dd>
        </dl>
      </div>

      <!-- Introduction -->
      <div class="prose max-w-none mb-10">
        <p>
          <a href="https://github.com/workos/auth.md">auth.md</a> is a markdown document at <code>/auth.md</code> that walks an autonomous agent through registering with a service: discover, register, claim if needed, present the credential, recover from revocation. It composes on top of RFC 9728 Protected Resource Metadata and adds an <code>agent_auth</code> block to the OAuth Authorization Server metadata. The agent never opens a browser and the user is never asked to complete an OAuth consent screen.
        </p>
        <p>
          This page walks the discovery half of the flow end to end against this server. Steps 1a and 1b execute real fetches: the Protected Resource Metadata and Authorization Server metadata are the same surfaces the <a href="/demo/oauth">oauth2 demo</a> exercises, with an additional <code>agent_auth</code> block on the AS metadata. Step 2 fetches the <code>/auth.md</code> walkthrough itself. Steps 3 through 5 describe the registration request, claim ceremony, and credential use as defined in the markdown document; the <code>/agent/auth</code> registration endpoint is not wired on this demo deployment, so those steps render the request and response shapes against the documented schema rather than against a live worker.
        </p>

        <h2>Protocol flow</h2>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Step</th><th>Action</th><th>Auth</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td class="font-mono">1a</td><td>Protected Resource Metadata (RFC 9728)</td><td class="text-[#999]">none</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono">1b</td><td>Authorization Server metadata + <code>agent_auth</code> block</td><td class="text-[#999]">none</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono">2</td><td>Fetch <code>/auth.md</code> walkthrough</td><td class="text-[#999]">none</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono">3</td><td>Register (anonymous · documented shape)</td><td class="text-[#999]">none</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono">4</td><td>Claim ceremony (OTP · documented shape)</td><td class="text-[#999]">claim_token</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono">5</td><td>Present credential as <code>Authorization: Bearer</code></td><td>Bearer</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Demo runner -->
      <div class="border border-[#e5e5e5]">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 border-b border-[#e5e5e5]">
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[#111]">Discovery + walkthrough runner</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-[#999] mt-0.5">Steps 1a–2 execute real fetches · steps 3–5 render the documented shapes</p>
          </div>
          <button
            id="run-btn"
            class="flex items-center gap-2 border border-[#111] text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.06em] uppercase px-4 py-2 hover:bg-[#111] hover:text-white transition-colors disabled:opacity-40 disabled:cursor-not-allowed"
          >
            <span id="run-btn-label">Run</span>
          </button>
        </div>

        <div id="steps" class="divide-y divide-[#e5e5e5]">
          {[
            ['1a', 'Protected Resource Metadata',          'GET /.well-known/oauth-protected-resource'],
            ['1b', 'Authorization Server metadata',        'GET /.well-known/oauth-authorization-server'],
            ['2',  'Fetch the auth.md walkthrough',        'GET /auth.md'],
            ['3',  'Register (anonymous)',                 'POST /agent/auth'],
            ['4',  'Claim ceremony (OTP)',                 'POST /agent/auth/claim → /complete'],
            ['5',  'Use the credential',                   'GET /api/... + Authorization: Bearer'],
          ].map(([num, label, hint]) => (
            <div class="step" data-step={num} data-state="idle">
              <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 px-5 py-3">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3 min-w-0">
                  <span class="step-indicator font-mono text-[10px] text-[#ccc] mt-0.5 shrink-0 w-4">·</span>
                  <div class="min-w-0">
                    <p class="text-sm font-medium text-[#bbb] step-label">{label}</p>
                    <p class="font-mono text-[11px] text-[#ccc] step-hint mt-0.5">{hint}</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <span class="step-badge font-mono text-[10px] text-[#ccc] shrink-0 mt-0.5"></span>
              </div>
              <div class="step-body hidden px-5 pb-4">
                <pre class="step-output bg-[#f6f6f6] border border-[#e5e5e5] text-[11px] font-mono text-[#333] p-4 overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap leading-relaxed m-0"></pre>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <div id="result-banner" class="hidden px-5 py-4 border-t border-[#e5e5e5]">
          <p id="result-text" class="text-sm font-medium text-[#111]"></p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[#999] mt-1">The <code>agent_auth</code> block on this deployment's AS metadata is what activates the auth.md flow; without it, a generic OAuth client sees only the standard RFC 8414 fields.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Technical notes -->
      <div class="prose max-w-none mt-12">
        <h2>Technical notes</h2>
        <h3>Where the agent learns about auth.md</h3>
        <p>
          Three independent surfaces all point at the same flow. An agent that reads <code>/agents.txt</code> sees <code>Authorization: auth-md</code> in the announcement layer. An agent that bumps into a 401 from a protected resource sees <code>WWW-Authenticate: Bearer resource_metadata="…"</code> and follows the pointer. An agent that already has the AS metadata in hand sees the <code>agent_auth</code> block alongside the standard RFC 8414 fields. Each path leads to the same <code>register_uri</code>.
        </p>
        <h3>Why three registration shapes</h3>
        <p>
          The three shapes (<code>identity_assertion + id-jag</code>, <code>identity_assertion + email</code>, <code>anonymous</code>) cover the three things an agent can prove about the user it acts for: a verified identity from a trusted provider, an email address only, or nothing. Each yields a credential immediately; the email and anonymous flows additionally trigger an out-of-band OTP ceremony so a human can confirm the registration. Anonymous registrations get a usable credential before the ceremony; the ceremony upgrades the scope set without re-issuing the credential.
        </p>
        <h3>Composition with oauth2 and agent-auth</h3>
        <p>
          The site's <code>Authorization:</code> directive advertises <code>agent-auth</code>, <code>oauth2</code>, and <code>auth-md</code> in the same line. The three are independent: an agent picks whichever it can satisfy. The OAuth metadata pair (<code>/.well-known/oauth-protected-resource</code> + <code>/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server</code>) is shared between <code>oauth2</code> and <code>auth-md</code>; the <code>agent_auth</code> block on the AS metadata is what activates the agentic registration flow alongside the classic client-credentials grant.
        </p>
        <h3>Revocation is provider-driven</h3>
        <p>
          The agent does not call a revoke endpoint. ID-JAG flows can be revoked by the provider posting an OIDC backchannel <code>logout+jwt</code> to <code>agent_auth.revocation_uri</code>; email and anonymous flows surface revocation as a 401 on a previously-working credential. Either way the agent's recovery path is the same: drop the credential and restart at the Protected Resource Metadata fetch.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer class="border-t border-[#e5e5e5] mt-4">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 py-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center justify-between gap-4">
      <div class="text-xs text-[#999]">
        <img src="/assets/wordmark.svg" alt="agents.txt" class="inline-block h-[16px] w-auto align-middle" />
        {' '}
        <a href="/spec" class="underline underline-offset-2 decoration-[#ccc] hover:decoration-[#999] transition-all">Spec</a>
        {' '}·{' '}
        <a href="/registry" class="underline underline-offset-2 decoration-[#ccc] hover:decoration-[#999] transition-all">Registry</a>
        {' '}·{' '}
        <a href="/demo" class="underline underline-offset-2 decoration-[#ccc] hover:decoration-[#999] transition-all">All demos</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-[#bbb]">CC0 (spec) · Apache 2.0 (code).</p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
function getStep(num: string) {
  return document.querySelector<HTMLElement>(`.step[data-step="${num}"]`)!;
}

function setRunning(num: string) {
  const el = getStep(num);
  el.dataset.state = 'running';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-indicator')!.textContent = '▸';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-label')!.classList.replace('text-[#bbb]', 'text-[#111]');
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-hint')!.classList.replace('text-[#ccc]', 'text-[#777]');
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-badge')!.textContent = '···';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-body')!.classList.remove('hidden');
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-output')!.textContent = 'Running…';
}

function setDone(num: string, output: string, badge = '') {
  const el = getStep(num);
  el.dataset.state = 'done';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-indicator')!.textContent = '✓';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-indicator')!.className = 'step-indicator font-mono text-[10px] text-[#111] mt-0.5 shrink-0 w-4';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-badge')!.textContent = badge;
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-badge')!.className = 'step-badge font-mono text-[10px] text-[#555] shrink-0 mt-0.5';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-body')!.classList.remove('hidden');
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-output')!.textContent = output;
}

function setDocumented(num: string, output: string) {
  const el = getStep(num);
  el.dataset.state = 'documented';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-indicator')!.textContent = '◇';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-indicator')!.className = 'step-indicator font-mono text-[10px] text-[#999] mt-0.5 shrink-0 w-4';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-badge')!.textContent = 'documented';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-badge')!.className = 'step-badge font-mono text-[10px] text-[#999] shrink-0 mt-0.5';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-body')!.classList.remove('hidden');
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-output')!.textContent = output;
}

function setError(num: string, message: string) {
  const el = getStep(num);
  el.dataset.state = 'error';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-indicator')!.textContent = '✕';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-badge')!.textContent = 'error';
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-body')!.classList.remove('hidden');
  el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-output')!.textContent = message;
}

const fmt = (obj: unknown) => JSON.stringify(obj, null, 2);

async function run() {
  const btn = document.getElementById('run-btn')!;
  const label = document.getElementById('run-btn-label')!;
  const banner = document.getElementById('result-banner')!;
  const resultText = document.getElementById('result-text')!;

  btn.setAttribute('disabled', '');
  label.textContent = 'Running…';
  banner.classList.add('hidden');
  resultText.className = 'text-sm font-medium text-[#111]';

  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.step').forEach(el => {
    el.dataset.state = 'idle';
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-indicator')!.textContent = '·';
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-indicator')!.className = 'step-indicator font-mono text-[10px] text-[#ccc] mt-0.5 shrink-0 w-4';
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-label')!.className = 'text-sm font-medium text-[#bbb] step-label';
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-hint')!.className = 'font-mono text-[11px] text-[#ccc] step-hint mt-0.5';
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-badge')!.textContent = '';
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-badge')!.className = 'step-badge font-mono text-[10px] text-[#ccc] shrink-0 mt-0.5';
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-body')!.classList.add('hidden');
    el.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step-output')!.textContent = '';
  });

  const origin = window.location.origin;

  try {
    // ── 1a. Protected Resource Metadata ───────────────────────────────────
    setRunning('1a');
    const prRes = await fetch(`${origin}/.well-known/oauth-protected-resource`);
    const pr = await prRes.json() as Record<string, unknown>;
    setDone('1a', `GET /.well-known/oauth-protected-resource\n\n${fmt(pr)}`, `${prRes.status}`);

    // ── 1b. Authorization Server metadata ─────────────────────────────────
    setRunning('1b');
    const asRes = await fetch(`${origin}/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server`);
    const asMeta = await asRes.json() as Record<string, unknown>;
    const hasAgentAuth = 'agent_auth' in asMeta;
    setDone('1b',
      `GET /.well-known/oauth-authorization-server\n\n${fmt(asMeta)}\n\n` +
      `─── agent_auth block ───\n` +
      (hasAgentAuth
        ? `Present. This is the block written for an auth.md client.`
        : `Not present on this deployment yet. The auth-md identifier is advertised in /agents.txt; the agent_auth block on the AS metadata is the activation gate. A real auth-md deployment publishes the block alongside the standard RFC 8414 fields:\n\n${fmt({
            agent_auth: {
              skill: `${origin}/auth.md`,
              register_uri: `${origin}/agent/auth`,
              claim_uri: `${origin}/agent/auth/claim`,
              revocation_uri: `${origin}/agent/auth/revoke`,
              identity_types_supported: ['anonymous', 'identity_assertion'],
              anonymous: { credential_types_supported: ['api_key'] },
              identity_assertion: {
                assertion_types_supported: [
                  'urn:ietf:params:oauth:token-type:id-jag',
                  'verified_email',
                ],
                credential_types_supported: ['access_token', 'api_key'],
              },
            },
          })}`),
      `${asRes.status}`,
    );

    // ── 2. /auth.md walkthrough ───────────────────────────────────────────
    setRunning('2');
    const mdRes = await fetch(`${origin}/auth.md`);
    const mdText = await mdRes.text();
    const ct = mdRes.headers.get('content-type') ?? '(none)';
    const bytes = new Blob([mdText]).size;
    const headings = (mdText.match(/^## .+$/gm) ?? []).slice(0, 8);
    setDone('2',
      `GET /auth.md\n\n` +
      `Content-Type: ${ct}\n` +
      `Bytes: ${bytes.toLocaleString()}\n` +
      `Top-level sections:\n` +
      headings.map(h => `  ${h}`).join('\n'),
      `${mdRes.status}`,
    );

    // ── 3. Register (anonymous, documented shape) ─────────────────────────
    setRunning('3');
    setDocumented('3',
      `POST /agent/auth\n` +
      `Content-Type: application/json\n\n` +
      `${fmt({ type: 'anonymous', requested_credential_type: 'api_key' })}\n\n` +
      `─── Response (200) — documented shape ───\n` +
      `${fmt({
        registration_id: 'reg_<id>',
        registration_type: 'anonymous',
        credential_type: 'api_key',
        credential: 'sk_demo_<credential>',
        credential_expires: null,
        scopes: ['spec:read'],
        claim_url: `${origin}/agent/auth/claim`,
        claim_token: 'clm_<token>',
        claim_token_expires: '<iso-8601>',
        post_claim_scopes: ['spec:read', 'mcp:tools'],
      })}\n\n` +
      `The credential is usable immediately at pre-claim scopes. The optional claim ceremony upgrades the scope set without re-issuing the credential.`,
    );

    // ── 4. Claim ceremony (documented shape) ──────────────────────────────
    setRunning('4');
    setDocumented('4',
      `─── 4a. Trigger the claim email ───\n` +
      `POST /agent/auth/claim\n` +
      `Content-Type: application/json\n\n` +
      `${fmt({ claim_token: 'clm_<token>', email: 'user@example.com' })}\n\n` +
      `Response (200):\n` +
      `${fmt({ registration_id: 'reg_<id>', claim_attempt_id: '<id>', status: 'initiated', expires_at: '<iso-8601>' })}\n\n` +
      `─── 4b. User reads the OTP from email ───\n\n` +
      `─── 4c. Submit the OTP ───\n` +
      `POST /agent/auth/claim/complete\n` +
      `Content-Type: application/json\n\n` +
      `${fmt({ claim_token: 'clm_<token>', otp: '123456' })}\n\n` +
      `Response (200, anonymous):\n` +
      `${fmt({ registration_id: 'reg_<id>', status: 'claimed' })}\n\n` +
      `The existing pre-claim credential keeps working; its scope set is upgraded in place.`,
    );

    // ── 5. Use the credential (documented shape) ──────────────────────────
    setRunning('5');
    setDocumented('5',
      `GET /api/some-resource\n` +
      `Authorization: Bearer <credential>\n\n` +
      `─── Recovery on 401 ───\n` +
      `Drop the credential and restart at step 1a (Protected Resource Metadata).\n` +
      `Do not stash and retry.`,
    );

    resultText.textContent = hasAgentAuth
      ? `Discovery surfaces fetched; agent_auth block present on the AS metadata. The full register / claim flow is wired.`
      : `Discovery surfaces fetched. The agent_auth block on the AS metadata is the activation gate; this demo deployment renders the documented register / claim shapes rather than wiring the /agent/auth endpoint.`;
    banner.classList.remove('hidden');

  } catch (err) {
    const msg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);
    const running = document.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.step[data-state="running"]');
    if (running) setError(running.dataset.step!, msg);
    resultText.textContent = 'Flow interrupted. See step above for details.';
    resultText.classList.add('text-[#c00]');
    banner.classList.remove('hidden');
  } finally {
    btn.removeAttribute('disabled');
    label.textContent = 'Run again';
  }
}

document.getElementById('run-btn')!.addEventListener('click', run);
</script>
